         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>On the day of the Jovian year Piṃgala, month of Kāṟttika, 2nd day, Wednesday, on the
               fifth lunar day, and the constellation of Puṣya, the Dhāraṇam-cum-Āraṇam of Cāmi, who
               is the servant of the servant, the servant-only, who enjoys serving the lotus-like
               feet of the illustrious Veṃkaṭābhūśāstriyaḷu, who is a receptacle of all sciences,
               the Sāmaveda, all auspicious qualities, the notorious embodiment of the explanation
               of the meaning of the Mahābhārata, the Rāmāyaṇa, etc. the eighteen Purāṇas, who
               enjoys serving the lotus-like feet of Mukunda who is being, consciousness, and bliss,
               sympathetic towards his own students, was copied with his own hand. </p>
         </div>
